{# HERO: marquee — the name as an awning or a hand-painted window.

   A bounded ink band carries the business name at genuine display scale
   between thin double rules; the headline, subhead and CTAs sit on the sand
   BELOW the band. The type is the image. The band is bounded rather than
   running behind the content, and the supporting copy leaves it entirely —
   which is what separates this from the category reflex (a photo behind a
   scrim with a centred white serif on top).

   Serves an established neighbourhood restaurant whose sign IS its brand and
   whose name is worth setting large.

   Optional config, all with fallbacks to fields every site already has:
     hero.marquee_word  → falls back to business.name
     hero.marquee_sub   → falls back to business.tagline
   An existing client's config switches to this variant without edits. #}
<section class="hero-marquee">
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="marquee-band">
      <div class="marquee-rules">
        <span class="marquee-word">{{ hero.marquee_word if hero.marquee_word else site.business.name }}</span>
      </div>
      {% set msub = hero.marquee_sub if hero.marquee_sub else site.business.tagline %}
      {% if msub %}<div class="marquee-sub">{{ msub }}</div>{% endif %}
    </div>
    <div class="marquee-below">
      <div class="eyebrow center">{{ hero.eyebrow }}</div>
      <h1>{{ hero.headline }}</h1>
      <p class="sub">{{ hero.subhead }}</p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="{{ hero.primary_cta.url }}">{{ hero.primary_cta.label }}</a>
        <a class="btn btn-outline" href="{{ hero.secondary_cta.url }}">{{ hero.secondary_cta.label }}</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
